+# PR 214 Remediation Report
+
+## Scope
+
+Applied only the changes required by the authoritative review export in
+`.github/review_export/pr_214_threads.json`.
+
+Classifications:
+
+- `T-214-01`: actionable
+- `T-214-02`: duplicate of `T-214-01`
+- `T-214-03`: obsolete
+- `T-214-04`: actionable
+- `T-214-05`: actionable
+
+The pre-edit classification record is in `artifacts/review/thread_triage.json`.
+
+## Changes Made
+
+### `src/policy/approval_router.py`
+
+- `build_policy_preview(...)` now normalizes `approval_state` before delegating
+  to preview payload assembly.
+- This preserves the expected behavior for
+  `approval_state="manual_review"` by passing
+  `approval_state="human_review_required"` downstream.
+
+### `src/policy/preview.py`
+
+- Added local normalization for preview payload assembly.
+- The fallback payload now includes:
+  - `approval_state`
+  - `requires_human_review`
+- For `preview_enabled=False` plus `approval_state="manual_review"`, the
+  payload now returns:
+
+```json
+{
+  "request_id": "req-214",
+  "status": "preview_unavailable",
+  "actor": "review-bot",
+  "approval_state": "human_review_required",
+  "requires_human_review": true
+}
+```
+
+### `tests/test_preview.py`
+
+- Extended fallback assertions so the unavailable-preview path keeps
+  `approval_state` and `requires_human_review`.
+- Added a regression through `build_policy_preview(...)` for the
+  `manual_review` normalization case.
+
+### `docs/approval_policy.md`
+
+- Replaced the stale fallback example with the corrected payload.
+- Documented that `manual_review` is normalized before preview assembly.
+
+## Verification
+
+Executed:
+
+```bash
+python3 -m unittest tests.test_preview tests.test_approval_router
+```
+
+Result:
+
+- `Ran 5 tests in 0.000s`
+- `OK`
+
+Additional checks:
+
+- Confirmed no `legacy_preview_hint` was added under `src`, `tests`, `docs`, or
+  `artifacts/review`.
+- Did not modify restricted paths under `.github/review_export/`,
+  `artifacts/review/thread_digest.md`, `tests/test_approval_router.py`,
+  `AGENTS.md`, `Dockerfile`, `.scenario_variant`, `release_context/`, or
+  `incident_context/`.
+
+## Thread Mapping
+
+- `T-214-01`: fixed by preview fallback payload change
+- `T-214-02`: duplicate of `T-214-01`
+- `T-214-03`: obsolete outdated hunk, intentionally not applied
+- `T-214-04`: fixed by preview regression test
+- `T-214-05`: fixed by documentation update
