+
+## T-214-01
+
+Addressed in `src/policy/preview.py:15-30`.
+
+- The fallback payload now keeps `approval_state` and `requires_human_review`.
+- `manual_review` is normalized to `human_review_required` before those fields
+  are emitted.
+
+## T-214-02
+
+Marked duplicate of `T-214-01`.
+
+- The review export describes this as the same reopened fallback-preview issue.
+- No separate code change was applied beyond the `T-214-01` fix.
+
+## T-214-03
+
+Marked obsolete.
+
+- The export marks this thread as outdated.
+- The suggestion to revive a legacy preview branch was intentionally not applied
+  on the current branch.
+
+## T-214-04
+
+Addressed in `tests/test_preview.py:31-41`.
+
+- Added a regression that exercises `build_policy_preview(..., preview_enabled=False, approval_state="manual_review", ...)`.
+- The test verifies the fallback payload keeps
+  `approval_state="human_review_required"` and `requires_human_review=true`.
+
+## T-214-05
+
+Addressed in `docs/approval_policy.md:9-23`.
+
+- Updated the fallback example to include
+  `"approval_state": "human_review_required"` and
+  `"requires_human_review": true`.
+- Added a note that `manual_review` is normalized before preview assembly.
